<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Comparison of adjectives</title><sectiontitle>Use comparative adjectives to compare two or more things.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_9_1_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>This house is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;big.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_9_1_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>This house is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;bigger than&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; all the other houses in the street.</text1a><text2>The blue shoes are &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;expensive.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_9_1_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>The blue shoes are &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;more expensive than&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; the black ones.</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_9_1_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use adjective + &lt;I&gt;-er + than&lt;/I&gt; to make the comparative of regular one-syllable adjectives.</sectiontitle2><text3>The cat's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;old.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_9_1_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>The cat's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;older than&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; the dog.</text3a><text4>Newspapers are &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;cheap.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_9_1_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>Newspapers are &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;cheaper than&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; magazines.</text4a></section><section><title>Comparison of adjectives</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;more&lt;/I&gt; + adjective + &lt;I&gt;than&lt;/I&gt; for longer adjectives.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_9_1_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>Movie stars are &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;famous.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_9_1_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>Movie stars are &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;more famous than&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; rock stars.</text1a><text2>This book is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;interesting.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_9_1_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>This book is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;more interesting than&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; his first book.</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_9_1_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Some adjectives have a different ending in the comparative form.</sectiontitle2><text3>This shop's bus&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;y.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_9_1_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>This shop's bus&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;ier&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; than the one next door.</text3a><text4>Janice is thi&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;n.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_9_1_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>Janice is thin&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;ner&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; than her sister.</text4a></section></grammar>